The paper deals with the exploration of graphs by mobile robots, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The exploration is done with time constraints and involves algorithms, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the possibility of unreliable robots, which requires the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
